Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{} to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @carrot{1}(grated on coarse side, no need to peel) and grate on the coarse side of your #grater{}. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded). Thinly slice and chop into small pieces. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150}.

When the water is boiling, stir in the @penne pasta{200} and cook for ~{12%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}. Pop back in the pan and drizzle with @oil{} to stop it sticking. Set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the shallots, pepper and mushrooms along with a pinch of @sugar{pinch}, @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until starting to colour, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, grated carrot and @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp} and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @tomato puree{30%g} into the veggies then stir in the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and allow it to evaporate. Stir in the @red split lentils{50%g}. Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}, @water{400%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{20-25%minutes}, stirring occasionally to make sure the lentils don't catch. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Meanwhile, drain the @mozzarella{1} and tear into small pieces. When the ragu is thickened and the lentils tender, stir in the cooked penne. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{}. Scatter the mozzarella over the top then sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Serve the veggie ragu pasta bake and enjoy.

> You won't miss the meat in this veggie ragu pasta bake. Made with a rich, tomatoey sauce, red lentils and stringy, melted mozzarella, this is every pasta lover's dream!